<TITLE> HC allows Mir Nasir to go abroad </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 18 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court on Sunday ordered the government to allow former state minister for civil aviation Mir Mohammad Nasiruddin to leave the country. The High Court bench of justices Nazmun Ara Sultana and Sheikh Hasan Arif also asked the government to explain why the bar should not be declared illegal. The order followed a petition filed by Nasir, a BNP advisory council member, who three days ago was barred at Shahjalal International Airport from going to Saudi Arabia to perform Umrah-Hajj. Barrister Mir Helaluddin, on behalf of Nasir, filed the writ petition challenging the legality of the prohbition. bdne
